1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've learned that when you've been sniped at, one fine way to prevent a war of words is to take a long pause before answering.

2
00:00:00,316 --> 00:00:05,086
Then I said to my student friend, much of what you say is true.

3
00:00:05,276 --> 00:00:12,365
There are many, many highly successful people who know absolutely nothing about the subject matter in this course.

4
00:00:12,716 --> 00:00:16,846
And it is possible for you to win success without this knowledge.

5
00:00:16,956 --> 00:00:22,125
In the total scheme of life, this course content won't make or break you.

6
00:00:22,316 --> 00:00:27,245
but your attitude toward this course may." What do you mean by that?" he asked.

7
00:00:27,436 --> 00:00:29,166
Just this," I answered.

8
00:00:29,516 --> 00:00:33,005
Outside, they grade you just as we grade you.

9
00:00:33,516 --> 00:00:37,885
What counts there, just as what counts here, is doing the job.

10
00:00:38,236 --> 00:00:43,486
Outside, they won't promote you or pay you more for doing second-class work.

11
00:00:43,996 --> 00:00:47,166
I paused again to make certain the point got through.

12
00:00:47,356 --> 00:00:50,446
Then I said, May I make a suggestion?

13
00:00:50,796 --> 00:00:52,765
You're highly disappointed now.

14
00:00:52,796 --> 00:00:54,926
I can appreciate how you feel.

15
00:00:55,116 --> 00:00:58,686
And I don't think any less of you if you're a little sore at me.

16
00:00:58,796 --> 00:01:01,245
But look at this experience positively.

17
00:01:01,515 --> 00:01:04,125
There's a tremendously important lesson here.

18
00:01:04,236 --> 00:01:07,966
If you don't produce, you don't get where you want to go.

19
00:01:08,396 --> 00:01:17,166
Learn this lesson and five years from now you'll regard it as one of the most profitable lessons you learned in all the time you invested here.

20
00:01:18,076 --> 00:01:23,806
I was glad when I learned a few days later that this student had re-enrolled for the course.

21
00:01:24,076 --> 00:01:26,846
This time he passed with flying colors.

22
00:01:27,116 --> 00:01:34,046
Afterward, he made a special call to see me to let me know how much he had appreciated our earlier discussion.

23
00:01:34,636 --> 00:01:38,525
I learned something from flunking your course the first time," he said.

24
00:01:38,636 --> 00:01:44,606
It may sound odd, but you know, Professor, now I'm glad I did not pass the first time.

25
00:01:45,436 --> 00:01:48,286
We can turn setbacks into victories.

26
00:01:48,476 --> 00:01:53,406
Find the lesson, apply it, and then look back on defeat and smile.

27
00:01:54,316 --> 00:01:58,525
Moviegoers will never forget the great Lionel Barrymore.
